The boyfriend of a woman whose headless body was found in Kempton Park, east of Johannesburg, has been arrested. The corpse was found in the woman’s flat. Reports say the woman’s head had been placed in the fridge in the flat. Police say they received a tip-off that led them to the woman’s lover. He was arrested in a nearby shop where he works. Police spokesperson, Jethro Mtshali says the suspect is due to appear at the Kempton Park Magistrate’s Court on Monday. 